Title: Bursts Detected and NOT Detected by EGRET Imaging Spark Chambers  
Author: Brenda L. Dingus Jennifer R. Catelli ; and E. J. Schneid 
Address: Salt Lake City, UT 84112  College Park, MD 20742 3 NASA/GSFC, Greenbelt, MD 20771 4 Northrop-Grummann, MS A01-26, Bethpage, NY 11714  
Affiliation: 1 University of Utah,  University of Maryland,  
Abstract: EGRET has detected the highest energy emission from gamma-ray bursts. Only a few bursts have been detected either coincident or just following the BATSE detected emission. These bursts are among the brightest bursts detected by BATSE. The EGRET fluxes, including upper limits, are consistent with extrapolations for all the burst spectra measured with Comptel. 
