Reference-contexts: FUTURE WORK The detection of even a few high energy gamma-rays has significantly challenged our understanding of gamma-ray burst sources. Bulk Lorentz factors of several 100 are required for bursts originating at cosmological distances in order to avoid gamma-gamma pair production <ref> [10] </ref>. The long time delays could be explained by shock fronts hitting an interstellar medium [11] or parts of the shock moving at slower speeds [12].
